<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
In males, 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. sparsipunctata" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="sparsipunctata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. sparsipunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognised by the shape of the labrum which is wide and rectangular (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 21–28" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 21 - 28. Andrena (Campylogaster) sparsipunctata sp. nov. 21 male profile 22 male genitalia 23 male face and labrum 24 male tergites. Andrena (Campylogaster) pruinosa succinea Dours, 1872 25 male face and labrum 26 male tergites. Andrena caroli Perez, 1895 27 male face and labrum 28 male tergites." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.974.54794.figures21-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/460645" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">23</figureCitation>
), whereas in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. pruinosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="pruinosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. pruinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is trapezoidal and markedly emarginate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 21–28" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 21 - 28. Andrena (Campylogaster) sparsipunctata sp. nov. 21 male profile 22 male genitalia 23 male face and labrum 24 male tergites. Andrena (Campylogaster) pruinosa succinea Dours, 1872 25 male face and labrum 26 male tergites. Andrena caroli Perez, 1895 27 male face and labrum 28 male tergites." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.974.54794.figures21-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/460645" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">25</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. caroli" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="caroli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. caroli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is less strongly trapezoidal and emarginate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 21–28" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 21 - 28. Andrena (Campylogaster) sparsipunctata sp. nov. 21 male profile 22 male genitalia 23 male face and labrum 24 male tergites. Andrena (Campylogaster) pruinosa succinea Dours, 1872 25 male face and labrum 26 male tergites. Andrena caroli Perez, 1895 27 male face and labrum 28 male tergites." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.974.54794.figures21-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/460645" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">27</figureCitation>
), but the tergites have well-marked and dense bands of short white hairs on the tergal margins (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 21–28" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 21 - 28. Andrena (Campylogaster) sparsipunctata sp. nov. 21 male profile 22 male genitalia 23 male face and labrum 24 male tergites. Andrena (Campylogaster) pruinosa succinea Dours, 1872 25 male face and labrum 26 male tergites. Andrena caroli Perez, 1895 27 male face and labrum 28 male tergites." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.974.54794.figures21-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/460645" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">28</figureCitation>
), whereas 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. sparsipunctata" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="sparsipunctata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. sparsipunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only a few scattered hairs on the tergal margins, never forming well-marked bands, as in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. pruinosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="pruinosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. pruinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
